sec.p:
Photovoltaic solar panel technologies can be divided into three generations [10], as follows:
First generation: Gallium arsenide (GaAs), and crystalline silicon (c-Si) such as multicrystalline (multi-Si) silicon and monocrystalline (mono-Si) silicon;
Second generation (thin films): amorpheous silicon (a-Si), CdTe, or copper indium gallium (di) selenide (CIS/CIGS);
Third generation: dye-sensitized, organic and multi-junction

